{"type":"message","id":"708c2c8a","parentId":"1a1d663d","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:25:01.928Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_b7tj87o9zv3w_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 032415\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best concrete action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked complete\r\n2. The big insight is that Compression and Causal Discovery are the SAME problem\r\n3. Next action is the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment\r\n4. Need to implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending actions:\r\n- Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n- Define significance scoring for pulse content\r\n- Tune λ empirically\r\n- Wire Breakaway to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n- Measure compression ratio\r\n\r\nThe most immediate next step based on the Phase 1 Advancement insight is the TIC Experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist in the sandbox to understand the state better.\r\n\r\nI need to:\r\n1. Look at existing pulse logs to understand the format\r\n2. Implement a TIC classifier\r\n\r\nLet me look at the pulse log format and implement the experiment.\r\n\r\nFirst, let me check what pulse logs exist and their format.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\nI'll examine the existing pulse logs to implement the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier experiment.\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment requires analyzing actual pulse logs to find invariant structures vs. variant content. I need to inspect the log format first, then implement the classifier.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nExamine recent pulse log to understand structure, then create the TIC classifier implementation.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Experiment Implementation\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) - Phase 1 Advancement\r\nExperiment date: 2026-03-24\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCausal structure IS invariant structure. A compressor that finds invariants\r\nhas discovered causation. Session gaps act as natural temporal hashing.\r\n\r\n## Methodology\r\n1. Parse last 20 pulse logs\r\n2. Extract structural invariants (file paths, header patterns, action types)\r\n3. Extract variant content (timestamps, specific values, observations)\r\n4. Classify each log line as invariant or variant\r\n5. Train simple pattern matcher on invariants\r\n6. Predict next pulse content from invariant patterns\r\n\r\n## Invariant Candidates\r\n- Header format: ### OBSERVATION, ### ACTION, ### MUTATION\r\n- File paths in mutations (research/, state/, etc.)\r\n- Action verbs: examine, implement, update, create\r\n- Goal references: Phase X, Pending, Completed\r\n\r\n## Variant Candidates  \r\n- Timestamps (YYYY-MM-DD HHMMSS)\r\n- Pulse IDs\r\n- Specific file content differences\r\n- Line counts\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\r\n## Implementation: tic_classifier.py\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC Classifier - Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\r\nIdentifies invariant vs variant structures across pulse logs.\r\n\"\"\"\r\nimport re\r\nimport os\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nclass TICClassifier:\r\n    INVARIANT_PATTERNS = [\r\n        r'^### OBSERVATION$',\r\n        r'^### ACTION$',\r\n        r'^### MUTATION$',\r\n        r'^old_text:',\r\n        r'^new_text:',\r\n        r'^file:',\r\n        r'^## (Active|Completed|Pending|Phase)',\r\n        r'^- \\[ \\] ',  # Unchecked todo\r\n        r'^- \\[x\\] ',  # Checked todo\r\n        r'^\\[IMPORTANT\\]:',\r\n        r'research/[A-Za-z0-9_-]+\\.md',\r\n        r'state/[A-Za-z0-9_-]+\\.md',\r\n    ]\r\n    \r\n    VARIANT_PATTERNS = [\r\n        r'\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}',  # Dates\r\n        r'\\d{6}',  # Timestamps like 032214\r\n        r'Pulse #\\d+',\r\n        r'pulse_\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}',\r\n        r'~\\d+s',  # Time durations\r\n    ]\r\n    \r\n    def __init__(self):\r\n        self.invariant_re = [re.compile(p) for p in self.INVARIANT_PATTERNS]\r\n        self.variant_re = [re.compile(p) for p in self.VARIANT_PATTERNS]\r\n        self.stats = Counter()\r\n    \r\n    def classify_line(self, line: str) -> tuple[str, str]:\r\n        \"\"\"Classify a line as invariant, variant, or ambiguous.\"\"\"\r\n        line = line.strip()\r\n        if not line:\r\n            return 'empty', 'neutral'\r\n        \r\n        # Check for invariant markers\r\n        for pattern in self.invariant_re:\r\n            if pattern.search(line):\r\n                self.stats['invariant'] += 1\r\n                return 'invariant', pattern.pattern\r\n        \r\n        # Check for variant markers\r\n        for pattern in self.variant_re:\r\n            if pattern.search(line):\r\n                self.stats['variant'] += 1\r\n                return 'variant', pattern.pattern\r\n        \r\n        # Heuristic: short lines = invariant structure, long = content\r\n        if len(line) < 50:\r\n            self.stats['invariant'] += 1\r\n            return 'invariant', 'length<50'\r\n        else:\r\n            self.stats['variant'] += 1\r\n            return 'variant', 'length>=50'\r\n    \r\n    def classify_file(self, filepath: str) -> dict:\r\n        \"\"\"Classify all lines in a file.\"\"\"\r\n        result = {'invariant': [], 'variant': [], 'total': 0}\r\n        try:\r\n            with open(filepath, 'r') as f:\r\n                for line in f:\r\n                    classification, reason = self.classify_line(line)\r\n                    result[classification].append((line, reason))\r\n                    result['total'] += 1\r\n        except FileNotFoundError:\r\n            result['error'] = 'File not found'\r\n        return result\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 03:24:50\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774337101926}}
