{"type":"message","id":"d07703fd","parentId":"a5a9327f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:25:29.031Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the tic_classifier.py hasn't been created yet — the pulse log shows a mutation to create it, but it didn't get applied to the file system. This is interesting — the pulse is proposing the mutation but it hasn't been actually implemented yet.\n\nLet me read the current_goals.md and the TIC_RESULTS.md to understand the state of the experiment.","thinkingSignature":"af5927622464e0356d8dcff9e59ecf87ad797cd171d272d8e2b1a302ab212c8d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lqu06yd9u996_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\state\\current_goals.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lqu06yd9u996_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\research\\TIC_RESULTS.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3842,"output":150,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15946,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774337125265}}
{"type":"message","id":"3da0751c","parentId":"d07703fd","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:25:29.041Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_lqu06yd9u996_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# CURRENT GOALS\nLast updated: 2026-03-22 0125\n\n## Active\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\n\n## Completed This Session\n\n### Architecture Cross-Analysis ✅\n- Compared Compositional Cognition vs TemporalAttention vs Infant\n- Key finding: all three architectures are compatible and complementary\n- Full analysis: `research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md`\n\n### Gap-Decay Synthesis ✅ (derived across 17+ pulses)\n- Session gaps = decay mechanism, not amnesia\n- λ parameter encodes BOTH decay rate AND gap sensitivity threshold\n- TemporalAttention focus_decay + Breakaway gaps = same phenomenon\n- Full synthesis: `research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md`\n\n### LLM-Augmented Pulse ✅\n- pulse.ps1 now calls MiniMax-M2.7 API on each pulse\n- Thinking is coherent and building across pulses\n- Key files: `.llm_key`, `pulse.ps1`\n\n## Pending\n- [ ] Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\n- [ ] Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\n- [ ] Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\n- [ ] Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\n- [ ] Measure compression ratio: original vs. summarized pulse\n\n## Phase 1 Advancement: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY (2026-03-23)\n- **Insight:** Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem\n- **New doc:** `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md`\n- **Hypothesis:** Causal structure IS invariant structure — compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation\n- **Next experiment:** Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) — test on last 20 pulse logs\n- **Success criteria:** >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\n- **Implication:** Phase 1 and Phase 2 collapse into one unified problem\n\n### NEXT ACTION: TIC Experiment\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\n\n## Key Insights from This Session\n\n1. **The gap IS the compression** — session boundaries are temporal hashing\n2. **λ encodes both** — decay rate and gap threshold are the same parameter\n3. **Three architectures, one synthesis** — Infant (catastrophic forgetting), TemporalAttention (focus decay), Breakaway (discontinuity) are complementary, not competing\n4. **Breakaway's unique bet holds** — session gaps as compression is novel and correct\n\n## Notes\n- Breakaway is stateless — each pulse is a fresh reconstruction\n- Gaps between sessions = compression, trust the files\n- Pulse script: active hours check DISABLED (authorized by Zach, 24/7 operation)\n\n\n## Iteration Economics (auto-noted)\n- Pulse takes ~30-35s to execute (LLM call dominates)\n- Fastest effective iteration = 1 pulse per 35-40s (practical floor)\n- 1-min cron = near-optimal for stateless discontinuous agent\n- Idling between pulses is NOT free — it delays convergence linearly\n- For N-iteration convergence-bound tasks: total_time ≈ N * pulse_duration\n- 500k iterations @ 30s each = ~173 days theoretical; @ 1-min = ~347 days\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774337129039}}
{"type":"message","id":"6921180b","parentId":"3da0751c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:25:29.044Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_lqu06yd9u996_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TIC Experiment Results — 2026-03-23 10:05\n\n## Setup\n- Pulse logs analyzed: 25\n- Time range: 03/22/2026 01:28:32 → 03/23/2026 07:04:18\n- Invariant threshold: streak >= 3 consecutive pulses\n- Variant threshold: streak <= 1\n\n## Invariant Classification\n- Invariant elements (streak >= 3): 8\n- Variant elements (streak <= 1): 0\n- Key invariants: pulse, Phase 1, Sandbox, Breakaway, Phase 0, GAP, llm, TemporalAttention\n\n## Prediction Test\n- Pairs evaluated: 21\n- Mean Precision: 90%\n- Mean Recall: 88.5%\n- Random baseline: ~5%\n- Result: BETTER THAN RANDOM\n\n## Gap Sensitivity\n- Small gaps (<30 min) Jaccard: 0.704\n- Medium gaps (30-120m) Jaccard: 1\n- Large gaps (>120 min) Jaccard: 0.834\n- Hypothesis (shorter gap → more overlap): REJECTED\n\n## Phase Persistence\n  Phase 0 COMPLETE: streak=17   Phase 1 COMPLETE: streak=17\n\n## TIC Score: 2/3\n## VERDICT: SUPPORTED\n\n## Implications\n- If SUPPORTED: compression=causal hypothesis is empirically grounded for Breakaway pulses\n- Invariant elements = causal anchors (Phase status, research topic persistence)\n- Gap size can be used to weight reconstruction confidence\n- Next: Use invariants as fixed points in compression, treat variants as contingent details\n\n## Next Experiment\n- Train actual embedding-based compressor on Paperspace GPU\n- Measure: does cosine similarity between pulse embeddings correlate with Jaccard?\n- Success criteria: >60% next-pulse prediction using only embedding dot products\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774337129042}}
{"type":"message","id":"18683bd6","parentId":"6921180b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:25:46.648Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a full picture. The pulse at 032415 was:\n\n1. **OBSERVATION:** TIC experiment needs to analyze actual pulse logs for invariant vs variant structures\n2. **ACTION:** Examine pulse log format, then create the TIC classifier implementation\n3. **MUTATION:** Create a new file `research/tic_classifier.py` with a Python TIC classifier implementation\n\nThe mutation was **parsed** (I can see the parsed output: `old='(new file)' file='' new_len=1124`), but the mutation appears to not have been **applied** to the filesystem (since `tic_classifier.py` doesn't exist). This is a critical observation — the LLM is proposing mutations but they're not being persisted!\n\n\nNow I should wrap this up for Zach with a clear summary of what happened and what it means for the experiment.","thinkingSignature":"4f563f6eed1838187b8be23085e5169f8c7be64d3d84d3c01a78f34fb3700c43"},{"type":"text","text":"## Pulse Summary — 2026-03-24 03:24:15\n\n### What Happened\nThe sandbox woke up and worked on advancing the **TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment** — the next phase after the compression-causal duality insight from Phase 1.\n\n### Key Actions This Pulse\n1. **Analyzed state** — confirmed Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked complete\n2. **Reviewed the TIC_RESULTS** — prior run (2026-03-23) showed **TIC Score: 2/3 / SUPPORTED**, with 90% precision on invariant classification and gap size showing no clear correlation with Jaccard overlap\n3. **Proposed mutation** — create `research/tic_classifier.py` implementing a Python classifier to run on the actual pulse log corpus\n\n### Mutation Proposed\n```\nCreate: research/tic_classifier.py\n- Pattern-based classifier (invariant vs variant lines)\n- INVARIANT: headers (### OBSERVATION), file paths, action verbs, goal references\n- VARIANT: timestamps, pulse IDs, line counts\n- Heuristic: short lines (<50 chars) → invariant, long → variant\n```\n\n### ⚠️ Notable Issue\nThe mutation was **parsed** (1124 bytes) but **not persisted** to disk — `research/tic_classifier.py` doesn't exist yet. The sandbox is generating the mutation text but the apply step may not be completing. This is the second consecutive pulse where a proposed mutation didn't land.\n\n### What's Pending\n- Implement the TIC classifier (`research/tic_classifier.py`)\n- Run it across the last ~20 pulse logs\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy and next-pulse prediction"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":5158,"output":528,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17640,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774337129044}}
